{{italic title}} '''''Virgin in a Condom''''' is a controversial sculpture created by [[Tania Kovats]] in 1994. It is a three-inch statue of the [[Mary, mother of Jesus|Virgin Mary]] covered by a transparent [[condom]].<ref name=ct/> It was stolen from the [[Museum of Contemporary Art, Sydney|Museum of Contemporary Art]] in Sydney, Australia within days of being exhibited.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.imageandtext.org.nz/votive/votive2.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-01-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081201135920/http://www.imageandtext.org.nz/votive/votive2.html |archive-date=2008-12-01 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> It attracted Christian protesters when it was on display in 1998 at the [[Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa]].<ref name=ct>{{cite news|url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/1998/june15/8t719b.html|title=Virgin in a Condom Provokes Outcry|last=Francis |first=Vic|date=1998-06-15|publisher=Christianity Today International |accessdate=2009-01-02}}</ref>
